---
import { AlertTriangle } from "lucide-react"
import Container from "../components/Container.astro"
import AnalyzerIsland from "../components/analyzer/AnalyzerIsland"
import PrivacyStrip from "../components/PrivacyStrip.astro"
import ReportCategories from "../components/ReportCategories.astro"
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
---

<BaseLayout title="Sekiro Save File Analyzer" description="Learn what the Sekiro save analyzer detects: Gourd Seeds, Prayer Beads, prosthetics, skills, key items, endings, and conservative boss status.">
  <article>
    <section id="analyzer" class="scroll-mt-20 border-b" aria-labelledby="analyzer-heading">
      <Container class="py-14 sm:py-18">
        <div class="mb-8 max-w-2xl">
          <h1 id="analyzer-heading" class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Analyze your Sekiro save</h1>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">Choose your <code>.sl2</code> file. Parsing and analysis happen entirely in this browser tab.</p>
        </div>
        <PrivacyStrip />
        <div class="mt-8"><AnalyzerIsland client:load /></div>
      </Container>
    </section>
    <Container class="py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="prose-page">
      <section>
        <h2>What the report includes</h2>
        <p>Every result includes a normalized status. Expandable details point you toward the area, source, prerequisite, or route choice involved without exposing internal mapping data.</p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <ReportCategories />
        </div>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Why boss results are conservative</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 flex gap-4 rounded-xl border border-primary/20 bg-primary/5 p-5"><AlertTriangle className="mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-primary" aria-hidden="true" /><p class="m-0">Boss memory items and candidate event flags are useful evidence, but they are not treated as reliable, persistent proof of boss completion. Bosses may therefore remain <strong>unknown</strong> even when related signals are present.</p></div>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Supported save file</h2>
        <p>The first release supports Sekiro PC save containers with the <code>.sl2</code> extension. The analyzer is read-only: it does not edit, repair, or replace your save. Back up important saves before using any game-modding tool, even though this analyzer never writes to the selected file.</p>
      </section>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
